From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: local build <local@orangepi3b>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 05:55:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] phy: guard destroy during failed DSI probe cleanup

On the Orange Pi 3B RK3566 vendor 6.1 kernel, enabling the DSI panel path
can make the Rockchip DSI probe fail while deferred probing is still settling.
The error unwind releases the internal DSI D-PHY devres object and reaches
phy_destroy(). In this vendor tree that can happen with a PHY device whose
sysfs/kernfs node is already absent, causing device_unregister() to walk a
NULL kernfs node:

  pc : kernfs_root+0x0/0x1c
  Call trace:
    kernfs_root
    kernfs_find_and_get
    sysfs_unmerge_group
    dpm_sysfs_remove
    device_del
    device_unregister
    phy_destroy
    devm_phy_consume
    release_nodes
    devres_release_all
    device_unbind_cleanup
    really_probe
    deferred_probe_work_func

Do not call device_unregister() for a NULL PHY or a PHY device without an
attached kernfs node. This avoids turning a recoverable DSI probe/unwind
failure into a system-breaking kernel oops.
---
 drivers/phy/phy-core.c | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/phy/phy-core.c b/drivers/phy/phy-core.c
index 3eeb2c2f68e2..38d3cad465bc 100644
--- a/drivers/phy/phy-core.c
+++ b/drivers/phy/phy-core.c
@@ -43,6 +43,9 @@ static void devm_phy_consume(struct device *dev, void *res)
 {
 	struct phy *phy = *(struct phy **)res;
 
+	if (!phy)
+		return;
+
 	phy_destroy(phy);
 }
 
@@ -1039,6 +1042,15 @@ EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(devm_phy_create);
  */
 void phy_destroy(struct phy *phy)
 {
+	if (!phy)
+		return;
+
+	if (!phy->dev.kobj.sd) {
+		pr_warn("phy: skip destroy of %s with no sysfs node\n",
+			dev_name(&phy->dev));
+		return;
+	}
+
 	pm_runtime_disable(&phy->dev);
 	device_unregister(&phy->dev);
 }
-- 
2.39.5
